Report for IDENTITY usage:
Doctrine IDENTITY → ORM 3 Migration: getId() null-check audit
Why this matters
With IDENTITY on PostgreSQL, the ID is assigned after INSERT (at flush), so getId() is null for a new, unflushed entity. If you resolve the deprecation by switching to AUTO/SEQUENCE, Postgres pre-fetches the ID at persist() time (before flush), so getId() becomes non-null immediately. Every place that treats "id is null" as "entity is new/not in DB" can silently break.

